14-03-12 14:07:31','2014-03-12 14:07:31','*  The main orphanage house at Merces has a leaking roof over the room in which  the kids have shelves to put their school bags and books.  The sisters would like to remedy this by constructing a covered terrace above this room which will also give a space to hang up all the laundry to dry.  Currently the clothes are washed by hand as part of the chores of the orphans.   There is no covered place to hang laundry for drying - so there is no way to dry clothes when it rains.    The estimated cost for this project is: _________\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01193-Small.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-233\" alt=\"DSC01193 (Small)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01193-Small.jpg\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n* The electrical wiring in the main orphanage house at Merces needs to be replaced.  Currently there are exposed wires and some of the wires are in disrepair.   The estimated cost for this project is:_________\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01195-Small.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-235\" alt=\"DSC01195 (Small)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01195-Small.jpg\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Current Needs','','inherit','open','open','','169-revision-v1','','','2014-03-12 14:07:31','2014-03-12 14:07:31','',169,'http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/uncategorized/169-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(375,1,'2014-03-12 18:18:15','2014-03-12 18:18:15','','DSC01136 (Custom)','','inherit','open','open','','dsc01136-custom','','','2014-03-12 18:18:15','2014-03-12 18:18:15','',162,'http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01136-Custom.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(372,1,'2014-03-12 18:13:24','2014-03-12 18:13:24','<a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01134-Custom1.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-371 alignleft\" alt=\"DSC01134 (Custom)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01134-Custom1.jpg\" width=\"320\" height=\"427\" /></a>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01136-Custom1.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-370\" alt=\"DSC01136 (Custom)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01136-Custom1.jpg\" width=\"427\" height=\"320\" /></a></p>\r\n                                                                                                               Gauri Shetty\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">                                      Tulsi Shetty</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">Tulsi was born November 2003 and her sister Gauri was born April 2005.  Both are living at the Sahar Orphanage.  They are in 3rd and 2nd standard respectively.  Their mother died in a road accident.  Their father had no job and was homeless so he brought the girls to the orphanage.   He hopes to collect them after they complete school through the 7th standard at Sahar,  by which time he hopes his personal situation will have improved.</span></p>','Tulsi & Gauri Shetty','','inherit','open','open','','162-revision-v1','','','2014-03-12 18:13:24','2014-03-12 18:13:24','',162,'http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/uncategorized/162-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(376,1,'2014-03-12 18:26:18','2014-03-12 18:26:18','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\"><a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01134-Custom.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-374 alignleft\" alt=\"DSC01134 (Custom)\" src=\"