l the orphans under their care.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSCF7190-Mobile.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-457\" alt=\"DSCF7190 (Mobile)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSCF7190-Mobile.jpg\" width=\"427\" height=\"320\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSCF7475-Mobile.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-464\" alt=\"DSCF7475 (Mobile)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSCF7475-Mobile.jpg\" width=\"427\" height=\"320\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThen, and even now, the sisters often arise at 5 in the morning and don’t retire till late at night attending to their missionary work diligently.  They have grown as an order from just 2 nuns to recently about 40 nuns.  About 10 of these are involved with the orphanages in Mumbai and the remainder are doing parish work in other parts of India.\r\n\r\nThe orphanages  have evolved gradually into becoming girls only orphanages today.  The boys  previously living there have all been placed with other orphanages or extended family.  For practical reasons it was not possible to have co-ed orphanages.  The boys were often disruptive around girls, not having any male residential mentors or father figures.  Also,  it was not possible to maintain separate living quarters for boys and girls.    There is  some ongoing turnover of the resident children.  Some of the kids leave if extended family eventually claims them.  Some of the kids leave because they don’t tolerate the structure that is maintained at the orphanage.  Most, however, stay several years, all the way up to becoming young adults that get jobs and even marry and start their own families.\r\n\r\nIt has always been important to the Sisters to educate the children in their care.  They have worked against many obstacles to develop a school at the Sahar Orphanage House which doubles as classroom spaces.   Over the years the school has become more widely attended by even  non-orphan children from the adjacent slums.  Today, 300 students representing multiple grade levels up to 7th standard are all packed tightly in a space not more than 2000 square feet.  When the school day is over the space reverts to being the living quarters for the 30  resident orphans and their caretakers.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSCF7229-Mobile.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-461\" alt=\"DSCF7229 (Mobile)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSCF7229-Mobile.jpg\" width=\"427\" height=\"320\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe teachers, who come from nearby communities,  are paid 400 Rupees ($ 7)  per month.  The children attending this school have no other viable school option.  They are unable to go to the already impacted government schools and nearby private schools are unaffordable for their families.  The HMBT school offers them a low cost education in subjects ranging from english, to science, to math, to crafts.  Were it not for this school, many of the Sahar slum kids would receive no education.\r\n\r\nAt the Merces - Giriz orphanages the girls all attend local independent schools, the cost of which is borne by the HMBT','History','','inherit','open','open','','141-revision-v1','','','2014-03-19 04:28:18','2014-03-19 04:28:18','',141,'http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/uncategorized/141-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(528,1,'2014-04-11 13:04:33','2014-04-11 13:04:33','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span id=\"sahar\" style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Sahar Slum Orphanage &amp; School</strong></span>:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Handmaids of the Blessed Trinity Orphanage, Rd. No. 2, Church Pakadi, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Sahar Village</span>, Andheri  East,  Mumbai  400099, India</p>\n[googlemap height=\"300\" zoom=\"12\" lat=\"19.1017135,72.8681533\"][marker lat=\"19.1017135,72.8681533\" title=\"Sahar Orphanage\"][/googlemap]\n\n&nbsp;\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span id=\"vasai\" style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><b> </b>Merces<strong>  &amp; Giriz  Orphanages</strong></span>:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Handmaids of the Blessed Trinity Orphanage,  Sapodi Wadi,  Kawlar Budruk,  Mari Naka,  <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Merces</span>,  Vasai,  District Thane   401 201,   Mumbai,    India</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&amp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Handmaids of the Blessed Trinity Orphanage,  Chauri Wadi,  Giriz Talaw,  <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Giriz</span>, Vasai,  District Thane   401 201,  Mumbai,  India</p>\n[googlemap height=\"300\" zoom=\"12\" lat=\"19.3599382\" long=\"72.7892803\"][marker lat=\"19.3599382\" long=\"72.7892803\" title=\"Merces Orphanage\"][marker lat=\"19.3715985\" long=\"72.7951597\" title=\"Giriz Orphanage\"][/googlemap]\n\n&nbsp;','Postal Addresses','','inherit','open','open','','481-autosave-v1','','','2014-04-11 13:04:33','2014-04-11 13:04:33','',481,'http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/uncategorized/481-autosave-v1',0,'revision','',0),(529,1,'2014-03-19 13:29:01','2014-03-19 13:29:01','Sahar Slum Orphanage &amp; School:\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Handmaids of the Blessed Trinity Orphanage</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Rd.  No. 2 ,    Church Pakadi,   Sahar Village,  Andheri  East,  Mumbai - 99     India</p>\r\napproximate Google map location of this site:\r\n\r\n[googlemap height=\"300\" zoom=\"15\" lat=\"19.1008466\" long=\"72.8674136\"]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMerces &amp; Giriz Orphanages:\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Handmaids of the Blessed Trinity Orphanage</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Sapodi Wadi,  Kawlar Budruk,  Mari Naka,  Merces,  Vasai,  District Thane -  401 201,   Mumbai,    India   &amp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"t