er.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01034-Mobile.jpg\" width=\"427\" height=\"320\" /></a>      <a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01022-Mobile.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-600\" alt=\"DSC01022 (Mobile)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01022-Mobile.jpg\" width=\"427\" height=\"320\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Giriz Orphanage:    </strong>\r\n\r\nThis orphanage is located about 2 Km. from the Merces Orphanage (<a title=\"Postal Addresses\" href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/contact/postal-addresses#vasai\">see location</a>).   It is the newest building of the three,  and is currently used to house the older,  most independent girls under the supervision of the Handmaids.  Currently about 7-10 girls reside here.   Here they have a chance to focus on their studies in school in a more quiet environment.   Across the road from this orphanage is the Giriz Formation House of the Handmaids of the Blessed Trinity Order.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01190-Mobile.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-608\" alt=\"DSC01190 (Mobile)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01190-Mobile.jpg\" width=\"427\" height=\"320\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Orphanages','','inherit','open','open','','222-revision-v1','','','2014-04-03 01:55:12','2014-04-03 01:55:12','',222,'http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/uncategorized/222-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(736,1,'2014-04-04 01:31:01','2014-04-04 01:31:01','','logo','','inherit','open','open','','logo','','','2014-04-04 01:31:01','2014-04-04 01:31:01','',0,'http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/logo.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(737,1,'2014-04-04 12:46:08','2014-04-04 12:46:08','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span id=\"sahar\" style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Sahar Slum Orphanage &amp; School</strong></span>:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Handmaids of the Blessed Trinity Orphanage, Rd. No. 2, Church Pakadi, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Sahar Village</span>, Andheri  East,  Mumbai  400099, India</p>\r\n[googlemap height=\"300\" zoom=\"12\" lat=\"19.1017135,72.8681533\"][marker lat=\"19.1017135,72.8681533\" title=\"Sahar Orphanage\"][/googlemap]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span id=\"vasai\" style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Merces  &amp; Giriz  Orphanages</strong></span>:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Handmaids of the Blessed Trinity Orphanage,  Sapodi Wadi,  Kawlar Budruk,  Mari Naka,  <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Merces</span>,  Vasai,  District Thane   401 201,   Mumbai,    India</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&amp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Handmaids of the Blessed Trinity Orphanage,  Chauri Wadi,  Giriz Talaw,  <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Giriz</span>, Vasai,  District Thane   401 201,  Mumbai,  India</p>\r\n[googlemap height=\"300\" zoom=\"12\" lat=\"19.3599382\" long=\"72.7892803\"][marker lat=\"19.3599382\" long=\"72.7892803\" title=\"Merces Orphanage\"][marker lat=\"19.3715985\" long=\"72.7951597\" title=\"Giriz Orphanage\"][/googlemap]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Postal Addresses','','inherit','open','open','','481-revision-v1','','','2014-04-04 12:46:08','2014-04-04 12:46:08','',481,'http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/uncategorized/481-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(738,1,'2014-04-11 13:17:35','2014-04-11 13:17:35','This page will profile recently funded projects.\n\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Completed October 2013</span>:    The rusting and broken down stairs at the Merces Orphanage house needed replacement.  It was the main passage way for 100 orphans to get to their upstairs living quarters.  The cost of this project was 232,500 Rupees (aproximately $ 4,850).   This entire project was funded by a single benefactor who wishes to remain anonymous.\n\n<a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01021-Mobile.jpg\"><img alt=\"DSC01021 (Mobile)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01021-Mobile.jpg\" width=\"427\" height=\"320\" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Completed late 2012</span>:   Power outages at the Merces Orphanage are frequent, almost daily for brief periods of time.   During this time a back-up electric battery system was needed to power several light bulbs.  The cost of this project was 52,000 Rupees (approximately $ 1100).   This entire project was funded by a single benefactor who wishes to remain anonymous.\n\n<a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/Invertor-cropped.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-767\" alt=\"Invertor cropped\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/Invertor-cropped.jpg\" width=\"550\" height=\"393\" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Completed Fall 2011</span>:   Water used for personal hygeine and washing clothes at the Merces Orphanage house was not sanitary;  it was also uncomfortably cold for bathing.  The reasons of this are described in <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">this section</span> of the Diary of a Visit narrative.  The solution involved sealing the supply well,  then filtering and pumping contaminated well water to a solar heated water tank installed on the roof of the orphanage house.  From here the water is gravity delivered to the first floor.  Not only is the water clean and safe but also warm for bathing in the winter months.  The cost of this project was 200,000 Rupees (approx. $ 4900).   The funds for this project were raised from many individual donors including the congregation of the Zen Buddhist Temple of Ann Arbor, Michigan.\n\n<a style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\" href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01049-Mobile.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-743\" alt=\"DSC01049 (Mobile)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01049-Mobile.jpg\" width=\"427\" height=\"320\" /></a>  <a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/Solar-Water-Tank.jpg\"><img alt=\"Solar Water Tank\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/Solar-Water-Tank.jpg\" width=\"320\" height=\"300\" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;','Recently Funded','','inherit','open','open','','509-autosave-v1','','','2014-04-11 13:17:35','2014-04-11 13:17:35','',509,'http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/uncategorized/509-autosave-v1',0,'revision','',0),(739,1,'2014-04-04 13:17:52','2014-04-04 13:17:52','This page will profile recently funded projects\r\n\r\nReplacement of rusting and broken down stairs at the Merces Orphanage house was completed in October, 2013.  The cost of this project was 232,500 Rupees (aproximately $ 4,850).   This entire project was funded by a single benefactor Dr. Judy Macy from Grosse Ile,  Michigan.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Recently Funded','','inherit','open','open','','509-revision-v1','','','2014-04-04 13:17:52','2014-04-04 13:17:52','',509,'http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/uncategorized/509-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(740,1,'2014-04-04 13:18:30','2014-04-04 13:18:30','','DSC01021 (Mobile)','','inherit','open','open','','dsc01021-mobile','','','2014-04-04 13:18:30','2014-04-04 13:18:30','',509,'http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01021-Mobile.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(741,1,'2014-04-04 13:19:17','2014-04-04 13:19:17','This page will profile recently funded projects\r\n\r\nReplacement of rusting and broken down stairs at the Merces Orphanage house was completed in October, 2013.  The cost of this project was 232,500 Rupees (aproximately $ 4,850).   This entire project was funded by a single benefactor Dr. Judy Macy from Grosse Ile,  Michigan.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01021-Mobile.jpg\"><img alt=\"DSC01021 (Mobile)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01021-Mobile.jpg\" width=\"427\" height=\"320\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Recently Funded','','inherit','open','open','','509-revision-v1','','','2014-04-04 13:19:17','2014-04-04 13:19:17','',509,'http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/uncategorized/509-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(742,1,'2014-04-04 13:53:41','2014-04-04 13:53:41','This page will profile recently funded projects.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Completed October 2013</span>:    The rusting and broken down stairs at the Merces Orphanage house needed replacement.  It was the main passage way for 100 orphans to get to their upstairs living quarters.  The cost of this project was 232,500 Rupees (aproximately $ 4,850).   This entire project was funded by a single benefactor Dr. Judy Macy from Grosse Ile,  Michigan.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01021-Mobile.jpg\"><img alt=\"DSC01021 (Mobile)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01021-Mobile.jpg\" width=\"427\" height=\"320\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Completed late 2012</span>:   Power outages at the Merces Orphanage are frequent, almost daily for brief periods of time.   During this time a back-up electric battery system was needed to power several light bulbs.  The cost of this project was 52,000 Rupees (approximately $ 1100).   This entire project was funded by a single benefactor Dr. Judy Macy from Grosse Ile,  Michigan.\r\n\r\nxxx PHOTO PENDING xxx\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Completed Fall 2011</span>:   Water used for personal hygeine and washing clothes was not sanitary;  it was also uncomfortably cold for bathing.  The reasons of this are described in this narrative.  A system was installed to filter and then pump contaminated well water to a solar heated water tank  on the roof of the Merces orphanage house.  From here the water is gravity delivered to the first floor.  Not only is the water clean and safe but also warm for bathing in the winter months.  The cost of this project was 200,000 Rupees (approximately $ 4900).   The funds for this project were raised from many individual donors including the congregation of the Zen Buddhist Temple of Ann Arbor, Michigan\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Recently Funded','','inherit','open','open','','509-revision-v1','','','2014-04-04 13:53:41','2014-04-04 13:53:41','',509,'http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/uncategorized/509-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(743,1,'2014-04-04 13:56:01','2014-04-04 13:56:01','','DSC01049 (Mobile)','','inherit','open','open','','dsc01049-mobile','','','2014-04-04 13:56:01','2014-04-04 13:56:01','',509,'http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01049-Mobile.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(744,1,'2014-04-04 13:56:52','2014-04-04 13:56:52','This page will profile recently funded projects.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Completed October 2013</span>:    The rusting and broken down stairs at the Merces Orphanage house needed replacement.  It was the main passage way for 100 orphans to get to their upstairs living quarters.  The cost of this project was 232,500 Rupees (aproximately $ 4,850).   This entire project was funded by a single benefactor Dr. Judy Macy from Grosse Ile,  Michigan.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01021-Mobile.jpg\"><img alt=\"DSC01021 (Mobile)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/w